largest publicly traded U.S. water utility, bought three water
and wastewater systems in Pennsylvania for $6.9 million.  The three acquisitions, two in Pike County and one in Adams
County, serve a combined 2,100 people, Voorhees, New Jersey-based American Water said in a statement yesterday.  The companyâ€™s Pennsylvania American Water unit has made six
